> Can you minimize the changes to the ones you absolutely need? We can do a separate cleanup checkin. Otherwise it gets very hard for reviewers

@mcvsubbu I started that way, but with boolean type return as well as exception inside the method, it becomes really hard to handle unexpected behaviors.
Regardless of the changes in tests, most of the changes are in PinotLLCRealtimeSegmentManager because the segment assignment logic needs to be replaced.
